Police are investigating after a woman's body was pulled from the River Clyde. Woman's body pulled out of River Clyde Police are investigating after a woman's body was pulled from the River Clyde.Emergency services were alerted around 8pm after the body was spotted in the water close to the Renfrew Ferry.Police, fire and ambulance were called and the body was recovered from the water.A police spokeswoman said: &quot;The body of a woman was discovered in the River Clyde at the Renfrew Ferry slipway, in Renfrew at around 8.10pm on Tuesday.&quot; 